FBIS4-46374 "jptot024__l94051" JPRS-TOT-94-024-L JPRS Terrorism FOUO 7 June 1994 NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA PALESTINIAN AFFAIRS Shin Bet Uncovers Attempt To Assassinate al-Rujub Shin Bet Uncovers Attempt To Assassinate al-Rujub TA0706181794 Jerusalem New Channel 2 Television Network in Hebrew 1700 GMT 7 Jun 94 TA0706181794 Jerusalem New Channel 2 Television Network Hebrew BFN [Announcer-read report] [Text] The Shin Bet several days ago uncovered an assassination attempt against Jibril al-Rujub, head of the Palestinian preventive security service. Al-Rujub, who was in Tulkarm that day, was informed he had better cancel a planned visit to Nabulus because he can expect an unpleasant surprise there. The tension between the Palestinian police and Hamas [Islamic Resistance Movement] in the Gaza and Jericho autonomy areas is increasing.
